    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Objects comprising upright wooden sticks with folded paper attached, forming a zigzag pattern on each side. The type of folding and paper varies based on the type of gohei and its related religious functions. Feature of Shinto practices; often placed in Shinto shrines or temples, either as an offering or as an indication of a deity's presence.</Note_Text>
